Question:
The surfaces in < image 2 > that can be obtained from the rectangular strip of paper shown in < image 1 > by gluing the arrows together are:

Options:
A: Only (a)
B: Only (b)
C: (a) and (b)
D: None
E: \\

message.content:
Arrows on the strip both point in the same direction along the length. Gluing the ends so that arrows match (same direction) gives a standard cylinder (a). To get the twisted strip (Möbius band, b), one end must be flipped so the arrows oppose; this contradicts the given direction. Hence only (a) is possible.

Answer:A
